            "description": "Infrared-divergent multi-scale 1-loop box with one doubled propagator (massive line, indicated by cross). One internal mass $m$, two on-shell massive external legs ($p_3,p_4$ with masses $m_3,m_4$), and two off-shell legs ($p_1,p_2$). Kinematic point: $p_1^2=1.2$, $p_2^2=3.1$, $p_3^2=m_3^2=2.7$, $p_4^2=m_4^2=7.5$, $m^2=5.4$, $t=-1.0$, $s=(m_3+m_4)^2(1+\\delta)=19.2(1+\\delta)$ with $\\delta$ scanned in $10^{-7}..1$. Computed numerically via the new auxiliary-mass-flow ODE method using a dimension-recurrence based one-loop ODE [Eq. (8)]; results given as a Laurent series through $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon)$ with at least 10 correct significant digits. Compared against FIESTA4.",
